Extract aggregated simulated data

Source: R/utilities-plotting.R
dot-extractAggregatedSimulatedData.Rd

Extract aggregated simulated data

Usage

.extractAggregatedSimulatedData(simData, quantiles = c(0.05, 0.5, 0.95))

Arguments

simData

A data frame with simulated data from DataCombined$toDataFrame().

quantiles

A numerical vector with quantile values (Default: c(0.05, 0.50, 0.95)), with the quantile values defining the aggregation of individual data. In the profile plot, the middle value will be used to draw a line, while the lower and upper values will be used to create a ribbon.

Details

The simulated values will be aggregated across individuals for each time point.

See also

Other utilities-plotting: .addMissingGroupings(), .convertGeneralToSpecificPlotConfiguration(), .createAxesLabels()

Examples


# let's create a data frame to test this function
df <- dplyr::tibble(

    0.280027687549591, 0, 0.26139160990715, 0.266613900661469, 0.271381109952927,
